Senate Resolution 395
By: Senators James of the 28th, Rhett of the 33rd, Orrock of the 36th, Mallow of the 2nd,
Esteves of the 35th and others
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Sheriff Melody M. Maddox; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Sheriff Melody M. Maddox has demonstrated an unwavering commitment to
3 public safety and law enforcement throughout her distinguished career, which spans more
4 than 20 years of service with numerous agencies in the metropolitan Atlanta area; and
5 WHEREAS, in 2008, she applied her expertise to the creation of the public safety office for
6 DeKalb Technical College, now Georgia Piedmont Technical College, where she became
7 assistant chief of police and was appointed thereafter as the institution's first female chief of
8 police, making history as the only woman to hold such a position within the Technical
9 College System of Georgia's 22 colleges; and
10 WHEREAS, in 2013, Sheriff Maddox left her position as chief of police to pursue her
11 long-standing goal of serving as an elected official in law enforcement; and
12 WHEREAS, she returned to the DeKalb County Sheriff's Office in 2019 as chief of
13 administration and was subsequently promoted to chief deputy, the highest-ranking
14 non-elected position in the agency, where she oversaw critical functions of the jail, courts,
15 and training operations; and
