16 WHEREAS, following the retirement of Sheriff Mann, she was appointed to complete the
17 remainder of his unexpired term and was sworn in as DeKalb County's 50th sheriff on
18 December 1, 2019, where she has since served with honor and distinction; and
19 WHEREAS, Sheriff Maddox's professional affiliations include the Georgia Association of
20 Chiefs of Police, International Association of Chiefs of Police, National Sheriffs'
21 Association, National Organization for Black Law Enforcement Executives, Women in
22 Public Safety, and the DeKalb County Chief's Association; and
23 WHEREAS, she further serves her community as a dedicated member of the DeKalb County
24 NAACP, National Council of Negro Women, Women for Morris Brown College, Saint
25 Philip AME Church, and Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority Inc.; and
26 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that gratitude is expressed for the unique and
27 often unheralded contributions of local law enforcement professionals on behalf of the
28 citizens of this state.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
30 recognize and commend Sheriff Melody M. Maddox for her exceptional service in law
31 enforcement and her invaluable contributions to the DeKalb County community as well as
32 extend best wishes for continued success.
33 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
34 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Sheriff Melody
35 M. Maddox.
